# Patch 0011 — Optional floating search + Kavacha dashboard new tab.
#
# Makes Zen's Cmd+T floating search a Settings toggle (Looks and Feel >
# "Open new tabs with the floating search bar", bound to
# zen.urlbar.replace-newtab, Zen's own pref — default stays true/Zen-like).
# When turned OFF, new tabs open the Kavacha dashboard instead: a calm
# Momentum-style page with a gradient of the day, a clock, a personal
# greeting (first-run name prompt, click the name to change it), and a
# daily quote from a bundled list.
#
# Privacy: the page is fully offline by design. No photos are fetched and
# none are bundled (the Momentum catalog the user liked is not
# redistributable) — backgrounds are generated four-stop gradients, twelve
# palettes rotated deterministically by local date. No weather widget: the
# original phones IP-geolocation + forecast APIs, which violates Kavacha
# defaults (and its icons are emoji, which Kavacha UI does not use).
#
# Mechanics, for future maintenance:
#   - AboutNewTab.newTabURL (resource:///modules/AboutNewTab.sys.mjs) is the
#     supported hook for replacing about:newtab; resetNewTabURL() restores.
#     KavachaNewTab.sys.mjs (process singleton, initialized from ZenStartup,
#     idempotent) sets it from the pref and tracks pref flips live.
#   - The page ships via jar (chrome://browser/content/kavacha-newtab/) and
#     may load with the system principal, where localStorage is unavailable
#     — newtab.js probes it and falls back to string prefs
#     (kavacha.newtab.*). The name never leaves the profile either way.
#   - New chrome package dir registers through zen-assets.jar.inc.mn, the
#     module through src/zen/common/moz.build EXTRA_JS_MODULES.
#   - Settings checkbox follows the zenLooksAndFeel.inc.xhtml pattern:
#     preference= attr + id registration in zen-settings.js + ftl string in
#     locales (update_en_US_packs.py syncs it into the engine).
# Applies on top of 0010.
# Focus (2026-07-14, revised 2026-07-15): the page originally stole focus
# after load because Zen's floating urlbar detached a search box over the
# dashboard the moment the view opened. The URL-row hardening (0010/0011
# iterations) fixed that detachment, so the steal is retired (user request
# 2026-07-15): a fresh tab now leaves the cursor in the URL bar, ready to
# type — typing summons the centered floating search, matching Cmd+T.
# Onboarding still pulls focus to its name input.
# Preload fix (2026-07-14, user report "still black after restart"): the
# preloaded new-tab browser is created for about:newtab's content process;
# the chrome:// dashboard cannot load there, so every new tab AFTER the
# first came up blank. Dashboard mode now sets browser.newtab.preload=false
# on the DEFAULT pref branch and evicts preloaded browsers on flip.
# Session restore verified: selected restored dashboard tabs render;
# background ones stay lazy until selected (stock Firefox behavior).
# Photo backgrounds (2026-07-14, user request): the day's Wikimedia Commons
# FEATURED PICTURE fades in over the gradient — same catalog the reference
# extension uses (2,548 free-licensed images; metadata bundled as
# featured.json, ~900KB; images fetched from upload.wikimedia.org at a
# bounded 2560px thumbnail, original as fallback, gradient offline).
# Attribution (title/author/license) bottom-right links the source. This
# single image GET is the dashboard's only network access;
# kavacha.newtab.network-backgrounds=false restores gradients-only.
# Favicon (2026-07-14, user request): dashboard tabs show the circle
# Kavacha logo (64px render of branding/kavacha/assets/logo-circle.png,
# bundled as favicon.png — the patch carries it as a git BINARY diff, so
# the apply steps must keep using plain `git apply`, never `patch`).
